#: ../../reference_manual/dockers/task_sets.rst:25
msgid "The tasksets docker has a record button, and you can use this to record a certain workflow. All :dfn:`Actions` can be recorded. These include every action available in the :ref:`main_menu`, but also all actions available via :kbd:`Ctrl + Enter`. Then use this to let items appear in the taskset list. Afterwards, turn off :guilabel:`record`. You can then click any action in the list to make them happen. Press the :guilabel:`Save` icon to name and save the taskset."
msgstr ""

